      "title": "Measures of digit span and verbal rehearsal speed in deaf children after more than 10 years of cochlear implantation",
      "abstract": "Objectives:Conventional assessments of outcomes in deaf children with cochlear implants (CIs) have focused primarily on endpoint or product measures of speech and language. Little attention has been devoted to understanding the basic underlying core neurocognitive factors involved in the development"
